In order to customize when to run change detection you need to inject ChangeDetectorRef and detach.

```
construtor(private changeDetection: ChangeDetectorRef){
  this.changeDetection.detach();
}

```
Then you can use an observable timer to run change detection periodically

```
timer(12000).subscribe(() =&gt; this.changeDetection.detectChanges())

```
Don&#39;t forget to manage the observable subscription an unsubscribe on component destroy.

Official docs: https://angular.io/api/core/ChangeDetectorRef

**EDIT**

to limit the number of change detection
implement OnChanges.
```
private countChanges =0;

ngOnChanges(changes: SimpleChanges){

 this.countChanges++;
 if(this.countChanges &gt; 1){
   this.changeDetection.detach();
   this.countChanges = 0;
    timer(12000).pipe(take(1)).subscribe(() =&gt; this.changeDetection.reattach())
 }

}

